<p><b>Game design</b> is the <a href="/wiki/Game_development" title="Game development" class="mw-redirect">game development</a> process of designing the content and rules of a <a href="/wiki/Game" title="Game">game</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Game_development#Pre-production" title="Game development" class="mw-redirect">pre-production stage</a><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> and design of gameplay, environment, storyline, and characters during <a href="/wiki/Game_development#Production" title="Game development" class="mw-redirect">production stage</a>. Game design requires artistic and technical competence as well as writing skills.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
